\chapter{Note:  Footnotes in EZ

}\leftindent{
The Note inset is intended to provide an alternative to EZ's default footnote 
style, which is occasionally somewhat cumbersome.  This inset will open a 
separate, scrollable window in which you can type the text of the footnote, 
and then you can 'close' the footnote, at which point the window will be 
replaced by a small icon, in an effort to keep from distorting the view of the 
page.   When printing or previewing, the text of the note inset will appear in 
the form of a numbered footnote.


