}\section{Creating a \typewriter{note} inset


}\leftindent{To insert a \typewriter{note} inset into a working document, 
position the text caret where you want the \typewriter{note} inset to appear, 
and select \bold{InsertNote }from the \bold{Page} menu card or type:


<ESC><TAB> n\typewriter{ote} <RETURN>


(the escape key, followed by the tab key, then "n\typewriter{ote}" when 
prompted for the name of the object, then the return or enter key.).  EZ will 
place a small window (See example above)at that point to indicate the presence 
of the note inset. You may then use all the usual EZ commands to put text into 
the window.

}
\section{Resizing a \typewriter{note} inset}

\leftindent{
Position the cursor precisely over either the right or bottom border of the 
window, until the cursor changes to a set of arrows pointing in towards a 
line.  Click and hold the left or right mouse button, and drag the border out 
to its new position, then release the mouse button.

}
